<p>I suppose I could counter by saying the number of depressed straight characters on the site is a cliche itself. Hell, we can boil it down to &quot;the number of depressed characters on the site is a cliche&quot;. I don't think I see it as a cliche any more than &quot;object what does a thing&quot;, because it's how you write it and put your stamp on it. And hey, I know not everyone will be behind this. That's fine. But to say that it's part of this new cliche of &quot;depressed and non-heterosexual&quot; character type is&#8230; is odd, to me.</p>

