															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1324229"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1461546506 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">25 Apr 2016 01:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2497265">
									

<p>Nice writing and three huzzahs for more queer characters, but beyond a few fleeting details, this didn't really feel like a SCP story. There's nothing wrong with slice of life stuff, but this could have taken place in a non-anomalous accounting firm<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-474997-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-474997-1')">1</a></sup>, and nothing would have changed.</p>
<p>While not everything needs to be &quot;682 fighting 106 on top of a mountain of clef clones,&quot; I do feel that articles on the site need to tap into the idea that <em>there is some weird shit going down</em> in some at least semi-meaningful way. I don't feel that this does. No vote.</p>
